cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about instance segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new framework that uses dynamic instance-aware networks, which involves machine learning techniques such as conditional convolutions and network conditioning. Hence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates its method on the COCO dataset, which is a popular benchmark for object detection and segmentation, indicating that cs.MM (Multimedia) could also be a relevant sub-category.
